==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bumble
<hw>Bum"ble</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Bump</er>
to boom.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The bittern.</def> <mark>[Local,
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bumble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Bumble
<hw>Bum"ble</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To make a hollow or humming
noise, like that of a bumblebee; to buzz; to cry as a bittern.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As a bittern <qex>bumbleth</qex> in the mire.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bumble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Bumble
<hw>Bum"ble</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>to act ineptly or without clear
understanding of what one is doing; to blunder; to stumble about; --
sometimes used with <ptcl>around</ptcl>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bumble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Bumble
<hw>Bum"ble</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>to bungle (a task).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bumblebee</ent>⟦br⟧
